<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1487,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,1487,1513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Description</emphasis>
. Length of body 
<number box="[507,557,1488,1514]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.9">1.90</number>
–2.00 mm (male), 
<quantity box="[782,955,1488,1514]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.6">2.60–2.80 mm</quantity>
(female); including forewing 3.00– 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.40 mm</quantity>
(male), 
<number box="[295,346,1525,1551]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="3.8">3.80</number>
–4.00 mm (female); forewing length 
<quantity box="[780,885,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.60 mm</quantity>
(male), 
<quantity box="[983,1088,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.20 mm</quantity>
(female).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1487,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,334,1562,1588]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Coloration</emphasis>
. Vertex, pronotum, mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[733,822,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[791,822,1562,1588]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) dirty yellowish brown. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1295,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[1264,1295,1562,1588]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) with basal half dark brown, apical half yellowish white. Genae yellowish white. Clypeus pale yellowish brown to brown. Eyes dark brown. Ocelli reddish brown. Antennae with first segment blackish brown, except median longitudinal band pale yellowish brown, second segment dirty yellowish brown. Thorax with sterna, including coxae of legs yellowish white to pale yellowish brown. Legs yellowish brown, speckled with brown markings. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[282,368,1749,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[338,368,1749,1775]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) pale yellowish white, almost hyaline, basal part uniform blackish brown and apical part from transverse veins to apex with blackish brown markings, nearly V-shaped, in dark portion veins bear short white stripe at intervals. Pterostigma blackish brown. Abdomeinal terga dark brown, pleura and sterna yellowish white to yellowish brown, except central area reddish orange. Pygofer and anal segment dark brown. Genital styles and aedeagus yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1487,2036]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,152,252]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,416,1935,1961]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">Head and Thorax</emphasis>
. Head including eyes wider than pronotum (
<number box="[936,998,1936,1962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.14">1.14</number>
: 
<number box="[1002,1013,1936,1962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
). Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1210,1936,1962]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[1180,1210,1936,1962]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) wider at base than long submedially about 
<number box="[444,509,1973,1999]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="3.46">3.46</number>
: 
<number box="[513,524,1973,1999]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[622,711,1973,1999]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[680,711,1973,1999]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) longer in middle line than wide at widest part about 
<number box="[1367,1414,1973,1999]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.2">1.2</number>
: 
<number box="[1419,1431,1973,1999]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
. Antennae with first segment shorter than second segment about 
<number box="[898,944,2010,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="0.5">0.5</number>
: 
<number box="[948,959,2010,2036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
, second segment cylindrical, longer than wide about 
<number box="[289,336,152,178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.5">2.5</number>
: 
<number box="[340,351,152,178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[497,582,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[552,582,152,178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) subequal to vertex submedially. Mesonotum longer than pronotum and vertex combined about 
<number box="[429,476,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.5">2.5</number>
: 
<number box="[480,491,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[633,719,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[689,719,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) longer in middle line than wide at widest part about 
<number box="[1355,1418,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="2.79">2.79</number>
: 
<number box="[1421,1432,189,215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
. Basal segment of digitus longer than second and third together, about 2.0: 
<number box="[1021,1032,226,252]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
