<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1223]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,390,151,177]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Male Genitalia</emphasis>
. Anal segment (
<figureCitation box="[593,782,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
Figs 20, 21, 
<number box="[750,782,152,178]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
) small, ring-like, ventral margin with a stout process medially. Pygofer in caudal view (
<figureCitation box="[578,720,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
) with opening larger in length than width, ventral margin concave medially, with two short lobes at lateral side, pygofer in profile (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1104,226,252]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1073,1104,226,252]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) with ventral margin longer than dorsal margin, posterior margin convex caudad. Genital styles (
<figureCitation box="[959,1140,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
Figs 24, 27, 
<number box="[1109,1140,264,290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) moderately long, widen apically, apical margin slightly concave. Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[794,943,301,327]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
) expanded at base, with aedeagus and phallobase. Phallobase developed, arising from base of phallus, median portion slightly expanded, forming a half sheath at apical half, surrounding aedeagus dorsally, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[998,1085,376,402]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
