<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1223]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,411,487,513]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">Female Genitalia</emphasis>
. Female pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[630,717,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 29" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,311,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[168,1404,306,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 29. Neobelocera lii Hou &amp; Chen, sp. nov. (17) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (18) Frons and clypeus; (19) Forewing; (20) Anal segment, lateral view; (21) The same, ventral view; (22) Male genitalia, lateral view; (23) Male pygofer, posterior view; (24) Male genitalia, caudal view; (25) Aedeagus, left side; (26) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (27) Right genital style, posterior view; (28) Right genital style, lateral view; (29) Female genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/275838/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[686,717,488,514]" pageId="10" pageNumber="49" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) with first valvifers moderately large, second valvifers long, broad and large. Ovipositor shorter than pygofer distinctly. Gonangulum small, apex blunt, connected first valvifers and apart from first valvulae.
</paragraph>
